    • registerBinaryHeap

      public static void registerBinaryHeap​(@Nonnull com.badlogic.gdx.utils.Json json)
      Registers BinaryHeap with the given Json object, so BinaryHeap can be written to and read from JSON. It may be problematic to register a custom serializer for the Node items of the BinaryHeap, so it's recommended that you don't; the output is more verbose with the default serialization, but it works.
      Parameters:
      json - a libGDX Json object that will have a serializer registered

    • registerAtomicLong

      public static void registerAtomicLong​(@Nonnull com.badlogic.gdx.utils.Json json)
      Registers AtomicLong with the given Json object, so AtomicLong can be written to and read from JSON. This primarily matters if you intend to read and/or write Random objects or their subclasses without registering a custom serializer for them. Although the EnhancedRandom implementations in jdkgdxds have custom serializers here already, and don't need this method to be called, other classes that extend Random are likely to need this if you ever run on Java 16 or higher.
      Surprisingly, this method is compatible with GWT, even though most concurrent code doesn't work there.
      Parameters:
      json - a libGDX Json object that will have a serializer registered

    • registerFourWheelRandom

      public static void registerFourWheelRandom​(@Nonnull com.badlogic.gdx.utils.Json json)
      Registers FourWheelRandom with the given Json object, so FourWheelRandom can be written to and read from JSON. This is (currently) different from the registration for this class in jdkgdxds-interop, because this needs to be in a format that can be read into an EnhancedRandom value by using a type tag stored in the serialized JSON.
      Parameters:
      json - a libGDX Json object that will have a serializer registered

    • registerTricycleRandom

      public static void registerTricycleRandom​(@Nonnull com.badlogic.gdx.utils.Json json)
      Registers TricycleRandom with the given Json object, so TricycleRandom can be written to and read from JSON. This is (currently) different from the registration for this class in jdkgdxds-interop, because this needs to be in a format that can be read into an EnhancedRandom value by using a type tag stored in the serialized JSON.
      Parameters:
      json - a libGDX Json object that will have a serializer registered

    • registerEnhancedRandom

      public static void registerEnhancedRandom​(@Nonnull com.badlogic.gdx.utils.Json json)
      Registers GapShuffler with the given Json object, so GapShuffler can be written to and read from JSON. This registers serialization/deserialization for ObjectList as well, since GapShuffler requires it. You should either register the EnhancedRandom you use with this (which is TricycleRandom if unspecified), use registerAtomicLong(Json) (if you don't know what type the random number generator uses), or just call registerAll(Json).
      Parameters:
      json - a libGDX Json object that will have a serializer registered
